cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular type expressions and an algorithm to decide their emptiness, equivalence, and inclusion.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper involves logical operations on type expressions.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper presents an algorithm, but it is less likely as the focus is on type expressions rather than data structures.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper deals with type definitions, but it is less likely as the focus is on regular types rather than programming languages in general.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possibility as the paper involves mathematical operations on type expressions, but it is less likely as the focus is on regular types rather than discrete mathematics in general.
